I forgot about that - target and start the mez, then immediately go to the next target, be it the next to be mezzed or back to melee.

If you are meleeing one and mezzing one, make sure you're not facing the mezzed one, and you can just leave auto attack on.  That way, you only have to lose about a second's worth of melee while you retarget and start mez, and target back.

